      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This Z06 is powered by the hand-assembled 7.0L LS7 V8, featuring a dry-sump oiling system, titanium connecting rods, and CNC-ported cylinder heads. The powertrain is mated to a rear-mounted Tremec TR-6060 6-speed manual transaxle for optimal weight distribution across the hydroformed aluminum chassis. The suspension remains tight, utilizing the factory transverse leaf spring setup with active handling and traction control systems fully functional. Recent maintenance includes a critical valve guide inspection and a fresh fluid sweep of the limited-slip differential. This is a mechanically sound example of American big-bore engineering, ready for spirited canyon carving or track day duty.",
